item.title: Cambage shelves retirement thoughts for WNBL return
item.description: Liz Cambage has signed with the Southside Flyers in the WNBL as preparation for one last Olympic campaign with the Opals in 2021 before potentially retiring.

item.title: SA records another COVID-19 case
item.description: SA Health will extend its active surveillance program as an “extra layer of protection”, testing some medi-hotel staff after another repatriated Australian returned a positive COVID-19 result.

item.title: Magpie swooping season starting early
item.description: Magpie season has started early this year and is expected to last until November, experts warn.

item.title: Byron Bay man fined for ‘extreme’ party
item.description: A man has been fined $1000 for breaching virus restrictions after he organised a doof near Byron Bay that was attended by more than 1000 people.

item.title: Cops investigate scandal-plagued MP’s wife
item.description: The estranged wife of scandal-plagued former WA treasurer Troy Buswell is being investigated by police internal affairs over an alleged “unauthorised recording” of him, a Perth court has heard.

item.title: Samurai murder accused’s $100k boost
item.description: Accused samurai sword killer Blake Davis has had his bail reduced by $100,000 after a court heard he resisted the temptation to flee when he accidentally broke his electronic monitoring ankle bracelet.

item.title: Ingles flying the Aussie flag as NBA playoffs begin
item.description: Boomers legend Andrew Gaze has urged the public to get behind Sydney-raised Philadelphia guard Matisse Thybulle as a token Aussie this postseason with Joe Ingles the sole Australian-born star in the NBA playoffs for the first time in eight years.

item.title: House fire leads to gun find, cop punched
item.description: A man has been arrested after a house fire allegedly led to the discovery of guns and a scuffle with police.

item.title: Confronting COVID warning for the young
item.description: A new ad showing how easily coronavirus can spread, and the potentially fatal repercussions of not taking the virus seriously, has been released by the Federal Government.

item.title: Bell’s case throws others into limbo
item.description: Eleven cases investigated by South Australia’s corruption watchdog are hanging in the balance because of legal issues arising from the prosecution of Mount Gambier MP Troy Bell, a court has heard.
